(
<figureCitation box="[159,244,452,478]" captionStart="FIGURE 37" captionStartId="78.[151,255,1898,1922]" captionTargetBox="[303,1280,227,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-79@78.[297,1290,210,1885]" captionTargetPageId="78" captionText="FIGURE 37. SEM micrographs of chaetae in Pomatostegus stellatus. Cuba, South-East, Isla de la Juventud, Cayo Boca de Alonso, 4 m, legit G. San Martin, ZMA V.Pol. 3840. A—“limbate” chaeta of 2nd thoracic bundle, B—Spirobranchus collar chaeta, C—1st row of thoracic uncini, D—middle abdominal uncini, E—Apomatus chaetae of 7th thoracic bundle, F—anterior abdominal chaeta." pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Fig. 37</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="77.[151,1361,529,584]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,294,529,553]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Type-species</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="Schmarda, 1861" authorityName="Schmarda" authorityYear="1861" box="[308,769,529,552]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Pomatostegus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="macrosoma">
<emphasis box="[308,587,529,552]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Pomatostegus macrosoma</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Schmarda, L. K." box="[594,769,529,552]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" pagination="1 - 164" refId="ref67329" refString="Schmarda, L. K. (1861) Neue wirbellose Thiere beobachtet und gesammelt auf einer Reise um die Erde 1853 bis 1857. I, Turbellarien, Rotatorien und Anneliden (2), 1 - 164." type="journal article" year="1861">Schmarda, 1861</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Abildgaard, 1789 Number" authorityName="Abildgaard" authorityYear="1789" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Terebella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="stellata">
<emphasis box="[984,1168,529,552]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Terebella stellata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Abildgaard, P. C." box="[1175,1361,529,552]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" pagination="133 - 146" refId="ref55105" refString="Abildgaard, P. C. (1789) Beschreibung 1. einer grossen Seeblase (Holothuria Priapus Linn.) 2. zween Arten des Steinbohrers (Terebella Linn.) 3. einer grossen Sandrohre (Sabella Linn.). Schrifter der Gesellschaft naturforschender Freunde zu Berlin, 9, 133 - 146." type="journal article" year="1789">Abildgaard, 1789</bibRefCitation>
Number
</taxonomicName>
of species: 3
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="77.[151,1437,632,1586]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
Tube white, opaque, semi-circular to roughly triangular in cross-section, with up to 5 longitudinal keels; granular overlay absent. Operculum a very flat ampulla covered with chitinous disk bearing a column with several serrated disks alternating with circlets of spines proximally and closely applied to each disk. Peduncle flatly triangular in cross-section with broad latero-distal wings along its entire length; inserted to the left or right at the basis of the branchial lobe; from the fact that the first and second radiole separated by the base of the peduncle, it is inferred that it is derived from the second normal radiole. Constriction absent. Pseudoperculum absent. Arrangement of radioles in (semi-)circles, up to 90 per lobe. Inter-radiolar membrane present. Branchial eyes present. Stylodes absent. Mouth palps absent. 7 thoracic chaetigerous segments. Collar tri- to penta-lobed, well developed with an entire smooth margin. Tonguelets absent. Thoracic membranes short, ending just posterior to the second row of uncini (segment 3). Collar chaetae 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Blainville" authorityYear="1818" box="[151,322,1018,1043]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Spirobranchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,322,1018,1043]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Spirobranchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- 
<typeStatus box="[330,385,1018,1044]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">type</typeStatus>
, with basal pilose fin and distal blade, and limbate (
<figureCitation box="[1001,1108,1018,1044]" captionStart="FIGURE 37" captionStartId="78.[151,255,1898,1922]" captionTargetBox="[303,1280,227,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-79@78.[297,1290,210,1885]" captionTargetPageId="78" captionText="FIGURE 37. SEM micrographs of chaetae in Pomatostegus stellatus. Cuba, South-East, Isla de la Juventud, Cayo Boca de Alonso, 4 m, legit G. San Martin, ZMA V.Pol. 3840. A—“limbate” chaeta of 2nd thoracic bundle, B—Spirobranchus collar chaeta, C—1st row of thoracic uncini, D—middle abdominal uncini, E—Apomatus chaetae of 7th thoracic bundle, F—anterior abdominal chaeta." pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Fig. 37B</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1844" box="[1130,1247,1018,1043]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Apomatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1130,1247,1018,1043]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Apomatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
chaetae present (
<figureCitation box="[159,268,1057,1083]" captionStart="FIGURE 37" captionStartId="78.[151,255,1898,1922]" captionTargetBox="[303,1280,227,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-79@78.[297,1290,210,1885]" captionTargetPageId="78" captionText="FIGURE 37. SEM micrographs of chaetae in Pomatostegus stellatus. Cuba, South-East, Isla de la Juventud, Cayo Boca de Alonso, 4 m, legit G. San Martin, ZMA V.Pol. 3840. A—“limbate” chaeta of 2nd thoracic bundle, B—Spirobranchus collar chaeta, C—1st row of thoracic uncini, D—middle abdominal uncini, E—Apomatus chaetae of 7th thoracic bundle, F—anterior abdominal chaeta." pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Fig. 37E</figureCitation>
). Thoracic uncini saw-shaped, with 9–13 teeth, anterior peg blunt (
<figureCitation box="[1080,1191,1057,1083]" captionStart="FIGURE 37" captionStartId="78.[151,255,1898,1922]" captionTargetBox="[303,1280,227,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-79@78.[297,1290,210,1885]" captionTargetPageId="78" captionText="FIGURE 37. SEM micrographs of chaetae in Pomatostegus stellatus. Cuba, South-East, Isla de la Juventud, Cayo Boca de Alonso, 4 m, legit G. San Martin, ZMA V.Pol. 3840. A—“limbate” chaeta of 2nd thoracic bundle, B—Spirobranchus collar chaeta, C—1st row of thoracic uncini, D—middle abdominal uncini, E—Apomatus chaetae of 7th thoracic bundle, F—anterior abdominal chaeta." pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Fig. 37C</figureCitation>
). Thoracic tori meet ventrally in larger specimens; in juveniles the ventral space between thoracic tori narrowing towards last rows that almost fused, leaving a triangular depression. Abdominal chaetae flat narrow geniculate, with long blade (
<figureCitation box="[159,265,1173,1199]" captionStart="FIGURE 37" captionStartId="78.[151,255,1898,1922]" captionTargetBox="[303,1280,227,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-79@78.[297,1290,210,1885]" captionTargetPageId="78" captionText="FIGURE 37. SEM micrographs of chaetae in Pomatostegus stellatus. Cuba, South-East, Isla de la Juventud, Cayo Boca de Alonso, 4 m, legit G. San Martin, ZMA V.Pol. 3840. A—“limbate” chaeta of 2nd thoracic bundle, B—Spirobranchus collar chaeta, C—1st row of thoracic uncini, D—middle abdominal uncini, E—Apomatus chaetae of 7th thoracic bundle, F—anterior abdominal chaeta." pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Fig. 37F</figureCitation>
). Abdominal uncini smaller than thoracic ones, with about 8 teeth in profile, 3 teeth in a row (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 37" captionStartId="78.[151,255,1898,1922]" captionTargetBox="[303,1280,227,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-79@78.[297,1290,210,1885]" captionTargetPageId="78" captionText="FIGURE 37. SEM micrographs of chaetae in Pomatostegus stellatus. Cuba, South-East, Isla de la Juventud, Cayo Boca de Alonso, 4 m, legit G. San Martin, ZMA V.Pol. 3840. A—“limbate” chaeta of 2nd thoracic bundle, B—Spirobranchus collar chaeta, C—1st row of thoracic uncini, D—middle abdominal uncini, E—Apomatus chaetae of 7th thoracic bundle, F—anterior abdominal chaeta." pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Fig. 37D</figureCitation>
). Achaetous anterior abdominal zone absent. Long posterior capillary chaetae absent, but posterior chaetae longer. Posterior glandular pad absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="77" pageNumber="78" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="77.[151,1437,632,1586]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,1288,1314]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Remarks.</emphasis>
According to the recent literature there is but a single circumtropical species, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Abildgaard" baseAuthorityYear="1789" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Pomatostegus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="stellatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Pomatostegus stellatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, an unpublished study by P. Valentijn (former student to HAtH, University 
<collectingRegion box="[1288,1381,1328,1354]" country="Netherlands" name="Utrecht" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Utrecht</collectingRegion>
), reinstigated two species regarded to be synonymous with the type-species to full specific rank: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Morch" authorityYear="1863" box="[1262,1429,1367,1392]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Pomatostegus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="actinoceras">
<emphasis box="[1262,1429,1367,1392]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">P. actinoceras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from the Indo-West Pacific Region, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Morch" authorityYear="1863" box="[629,744,1405,1430]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Pomatostegus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="kroyeri">
<emphasis box="[629,744,1405,1430]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">P. krøyeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from tropical Pacific America, leaving a tropical Atlantic distribution only for 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Abildgaard" baseAuthorityYear="1789" box="[396,523,1444,1469]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Pomatostegus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="stellatus">
<emphasis box="[396,523,1444,1469]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">P. stellatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The latter taxon has been recorded from Atlantic Africa by 
<bibRefCitation author="Augener, H." box="[1242,1431,1444,1470]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" refId="ref55547" refString="Augener, H. (1918) Polychaeta. In: Michaelsen, W. &amp; Friedrichsen, L. (Eds.), Beitragen zur Kenntnis der Meeresfauna Westafrikas, Vol. 2. Friedrichsen, Hamburg, pp. 69 - 625." type="book" year="1918">Augener (1918)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Amoureux, L." box="[151,368,1483,1509]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" pagination="41 - 65" refId="ref55255" refString="Amoureux, L. (1973) Quelques annelides polychetes de l'Afrique occidentale et equatoriale. Cahiers O. R. S. T. O. M., Oceanographie, 11, 1, 41 - 65." type="journal article" year="1973">Amoureux (1973)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Zibrowius, H." box="[438,665,1483,1509]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" pagination="1 - 93" refId="ref69840" refString="Zibrowius, H. (1973 b) Serpulidae (Annelida Polychaeta) des cotes ouest de l'Afrique et des Archipels Voisins. Musee Royal de l'Afrique Centrale, Tervuren, Belgique Annales, Serie 8, Sciences Zoologiques, 207, 1 - 93." type="journal article" year="1973">Zibrowius (1973b)</bibRefCitation>
, however, the single specimen studied from Western Africa by Valentijn and ten Hove could not be attributed with certainty to either 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Morch" authorityYear="1863" box="[1000,1167,1521,1546]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Pomatostegus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="actinoceras">
<emphasis box="[1000,1167,1521,1546]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">P. actinoceras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(likely) or 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Abildgaard" baseAuthorityYear="1789" box="[1307,1436,1521,1546]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Pomatostegus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="stellatus">
<emphasis box="[1307,1436,1521,1546]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">P. stellatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(less likely).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="77.[151,1436,1637,1779]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
1. 
<taxonomicName authority="Morch, 1863" authorityName="Morch" authorityYear="1863" box="[181,655,1637,1663]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Pomatostegus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="actinoceras">
<emphasis box="[181,490,1637,1662]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Pomatostegus actinoceras</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Morch, O. A. L." box="[500,655,1637,1663]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" pagination="347 - 470" refId="ref64593" refString="Morch, O. A. L. (1863) Revisio critica Serpulidarum. Et bidrag til rorormenes naturhistorie. Naturhistorisk Tidsskrift Henrik Kroyer, Kobenhavn (Ser. 3), 1, 347 - 470." type="journal article" year="1863">Mörch, 1863</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, Indo-West Pacific,?Western Africa; generally synonymised with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Abildgaard" baseAuthorityYear="1789" box="[188,315,1676,1701]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Pomatostegus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="stellatus">
<emphasis box="[188,315,1676,1701]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">P.stellatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="77.[151,1436,1637,1779]" box="[151,1376,1715,1741]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
2. 
<taxonomicName authority="Morch, 1863" authorityName="Morch" authorityYear="1863" box="[180,598,1715,1741]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Pomatostegus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="kroyeri">
<emphasis box="[180,436,1715,1740]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Pomatostegus krøyeri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Morch, O. A. L." box="[444,598,1715,1741]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" pagination="347 - 470" refId="ref64593" refString="Morch, O. A. L. (1863) Revisio critica Serpulidarum. Et bidrag til rorormenes naturhistorie. Naturhistorisk Tidsskrift Henrik Kroyer, Kobenhavn (Ser. 3), 1, 347 - 470." type="journal article" year="1863">Mörch, 1863</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, tropical Pacific America; generally synonymised with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Abildgaard" baseAuthorityYear="1789" box="[1249,1376,1715,1740]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Pomatostegus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="stellatus">
<emphasis box="[1249,1376,1715,1740]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">P. stellatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="77.[151,1436,1637,1779]" box="[151,1431,1753,1779]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
3. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Abildgaard, 1789)" baseAuthorityName="Abildgaard" baseAuthorityYear="1789" box="[180,684,1753,1779]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Pomatostegus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="stellatus">
<emphasis box="[180,450,1753,1778]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Pomatostegus stellatus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Abildgaard, P. C." box="[465,675,1753,1779]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" pagination="133 - 146" refId="ref55105" refString="Abildgaard, P. C. (1789) Beschreibung 1. einer grossen Seeblase (Holothuria Priapus Linn.) 2. zween Arten des Steinbohrers (Terebella Linn.) 3. einer grossen Sandrohre (Sabella Linn.). Schrifter der Gesellschaft naturforschender Freunde zu Berlin, 9, 133 - 146." type="journal article" year="1789">Abildgaard, 1789</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, West Indies; Caribbean; usually including preceding 2 species.
</paragraph>
